  <div class="about">
      <div class="use">

    <h4>How to use?</h4>
    <h5><strong>Step By Step:</strong></h5>

    <h4>1: Open app, and fill out your profile.
    Located at top right. It is important to fill our your personal information so that when the alert triggers, rescuers will be able to identify you.<br>
    2: Set your
    time duration.
    Located at
    bottom left. Setting your breathing limit is required. Once the watch detects that you are in contact to water, it will automatically starts to countdown. The alert triggers before your limit.<br>
    3: Alert notice
    when a nearby
    is drowning. Simply click their mark,
    it will show you the user’s data.
    You will be able to contact
    their friends or realatives.</h4><br>
  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="work">
    <h4>How does it work?</h4>
    <h4>The watch is attached with
    a mini Arduino chip inside, making it able to sense
    when interacting with water. It is placed underneath, with alert light. <br>

    The alert light, when on screen displayed, the brightness is automated to 100%, making it to have a bright light to murky waters or at night. The alert system is only triggered just before the user’s breathing limit. <br>

    It also includes GPS Tracker and sending coordinates to nearby users or rescuers. <br>

    Your location or coordinates is always on private. It will automatically go oon public and shared to nearby users and rescuers.</h4><br>
        </div>

    <div class="features"> 
      <h4>Features:</h4>
